OL,7,FOn the day the final report was
OL,8,Fpublished, Sir Keir Starmer apologised
OL,9,F"on behalf of the British state to
OL,10,Feach and every one" of the people
OL,11,Faffected by the disaster.
OL,13,FSpeaking in Parliament at the time as
OL,14,Fsome bereaved watched from the Commons
OL,15,Fgallery, he said the "country failed
OL,16,Fto discharge its most fundamental
OL,17,Fduty, to protect you and your loved
OL,18,Fones, the people that we are here to
OL,19,Fserve".
OL,26,@qD@AOUrD@SO]wD@VOU{D@FO]
